{
  "stem": "1033.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is George Scott.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was George-- or Gyorgy-- Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Hungarian, it's Spiegel-- George Laszlo-- Laszly-- Leslie is my middle name.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in Budapest on the 25th of May, 1930.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am still 64, barely.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can you go on and take us back to Budapest when you were a child and tell us what it was like growing up?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's a long time ago.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yet I remember things vividly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even when I was very young, I remember walking along my mother's side-- excuse me-- whining and crying nonstop.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she picked me up, and she was exasperated with me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was less than two.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father died when I was a year old.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I, unfortunately, had never known him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- Can you tell us your mother's and father's name please?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Emil Spiegel, Emil.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a-- a soldier in the First World War and collected some sort of sickness while in prison in Russia, and unfortunately, died from it around 1931.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was born in 1930.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My mother and father got married in Budapest in 1923.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I wasn't born for seven years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm awfully happy that I did make it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's name was Sara, She was the third sister of a group of six sisters born to my grandfather and grandmother, her mother and father, by the name of Reich, Mondi and Ilona.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my grandmother's maiden name was Wohl, W-O-H-L, W-O-H-L.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I remember she loved to sing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She loved to be happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was, I think, affectionate when she was well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And unfortunately, she couldn't do it on her own in the big city after she lost her husband, my father.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she went back in 1932 to a little village called Szucsi.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's about 60, 80 kilometers from Budapest, where my grandparents owned a farm.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had, I think, 300 acres of vineyards and 200 acres of land of sorts, and raised, I think, four of their six daughters in this village.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother was born in 1900.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother, from stories I gather, was a very sensitive girl, and she didn't get along too well with her father, who was super religious.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my mother, I remember, read Oscar Wilde and other authors.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in this time in Hungary, that wasn't the normal thing to do.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember her sisters mocking her, saying that she considered herself too good to live on the farm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And these sort of thoughts come to me much, much later on reflection.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At the time I, of course, didn't understand anything like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All I knew was that I missed her affection very much.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she too, unfortunately, leaves a large gap in my own life in terms of having had a mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We went to-- to live with my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I remember crawling on the floor of the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I remember, strangely, the underside of things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I remember how-- how big people's feet were, and how when I looked up their behind was there, and way up there was up the person.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was a person who seemed to have absorbed everything like a blotting paper.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And even though I didn't know what to do with the information, it was there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I spent a lot of time by myself.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My grandfather was the father figure in my life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was super religious and a nervous man who had to think of money all the time, paying the people who worked the farm, and then having dowries.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Two of the daughters-- my mother was one of them-- lost their husbands.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One, Aunt Margo, managed to remarry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my mother didn't, and she got sick, and was put to a hospital in the place called [NON-ENGLISH] around 1937, at which point I was in grade one, or grade two of the public school that the village had.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was the only Jew in this school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My teacher's name was Rosie.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I always felt strange.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All my life I felt strange being a child.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think primarily because other kids had moms and dads, and I didn't.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I thought that that was a terrible injustice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And even at school, I was kind of sitting by myself, taking things in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't-- I had one good friend, who we are still friends.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "His name is John Maksa, M-A-K-S-A.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He lives now in the next village.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In those days, used to be called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now it's called [NON-ENGLISH] Saint Martin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's about 4 kilometers to-- from the village where we grew up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Their house was the other side of the road from me, and we used to play horses and wagons.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we used to hide in the hay.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was great.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
